## X2 — Spec Conversion Gap Audit (Post-Write)
**Status:** draft

After converting `docs/design/forge-specs-relay-frontend.md` into formal specs, a gap audit identified missing component designs and an undocumented SSE routing contract.

| Gap | Severity | Resolution | Location |
|---|---|---|---|
| `GateBanner` component (Specs view sticky gate banner) | High | New Design D15 | `designs.ad` |
| `GatePanel` component (Relay view gate approval) | High | New Design D16 | `designs.ad` |
| `ReportCard` component (terminal completion in chat) | High | New Design D17 | `designs.ad` |
| SSE Event Map / Frontend Integration | Critical | New Design D18 | `designs.ad` |
| Open questions untracked (sound, escalation, persistence, locking) | Medium | Added as plan risks | `plans.ad` (P8, P11, P12) |

- Sound design: opt-in chime for gates?
- Gate escalation: browser notification after >30min?
- Secretary queue persistence across refresh (backend dependency)
- Multi-run document locking (ETag strategy)

All P0 gaps are now closed. The 4 new designs (D15–D18) and 3 additional plan risks provide sufficient detail for the Coder to begin implementation.

---

## X3 — Frontend Gap Closure Report (Post-Implementation)
**Status:** draft

All identified gaps from X2 have been implemented and verified. The frontend now supports the complete Smart Secretary pattern, live pipeline visualization, specs workspace depth, mode-aware gate filtering, and mobile-responsive accessibility.

| Gap | Status | Evidence |
|---|---|---|
| P8: ReportCard trigger | ✅ Closed | `setEventCallbacks({ onReport })` in `ChatsView.vue` |
| P9: Live Log data | ✅ Closed | `_liveLog` populated from SSE in `useRelay.ts` |
| P9: Per-profession Cost Breakdown | ✅ Closed | `professionTokens` ref + bars in `AgentsView.vue` |
| P10: Drift check visualization | ✅ Closed | `driftResult` panel with severity colors in `SpecsView.vue` |
| P11: Mode toggle filters gates | ✅ Closed | `useForgeMode` + `showGatePanel` computed |
| P11: Event router in useForge SSE | ✅ Closed | `useEventRouter` wired into `streamResponse` |
| P12: Mobile bottom sheets | ✅ Closed | `@media (max-width: 768px)` across all views |
| P12: Focus management | ✅ Closed | `approveBtnRef` + `onMounted` in `GateCard.vue` |
| P12: Screen reader annotations | ✅ Closed | `aria-label` on pipeline steps + `aria-live` region |

